text: Taray District is one of eight districts of the Calca Province in the Cusco Region in Peru. Its main city is Taray. The town is southwest of Pisac. It is near a stream named Pawayuq (Pahuayoc) that is part of the Willkanuta River. == Geography == Some of the tallest mountains in the district are: * Hatun Pukara * Inti Qaqa * Ñust'apata * Pata Q'asa * Pillku Urqu * Silla Q'asa * Wanakawri * Yana Qaqa == Ethnic groups == Many people in the district are indigenous Quechua. Quechua is the language most used in childhood (86.14%). 13.37% of people started speaking using the Spanish language (2007 Peru Census).inei.gob.pe INEI, Peru, Censos Nacionales 2007, Frequencias: Preguntas de Población == See also == * Mawk'ataray == References == Category:Pages using gadget WikiMiniAtlas Category:Peru
